               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 4 items (a-d)</head>
               <msContents class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2001009476 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of works on Shaṭṭārī and esoteric Sufism, comprised of several heterogeneous fragments from separate sources. 
Volume not dated; item c dated (Rajab 1223/August 1808). 
Scribal nastaʿlīq and naskh by multiple hands. 
Extensive annotations in margins and in interlinear spaces. 
Discontinuous foliation in pencil. 
Lacking original binding. 
Binding damaged (tooled and painted brown leather over delaminating pasteboards, revealing fragments from <title>Qurʾān</title> leaves and Arabic verses; wormholes), labelled. Additional loose paper wrapper (letter dated 18 October 1845 requesting translation from Arabic); watermarked (lion rampant guardant holding sceptre in crowned oval frame; not dated); torn, creased, stained. 
Folios mostly bound; cropped, wormholes, later repairs. 
Condition fragile. 
                  </summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_81A-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="1v">ff. 1r-1v </locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 81A a. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of notes on different kinds of revelations and manifestations based on awrād or the pronouncements ascribed to <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656451.0x000001 viaf_19540626" role="att">Shāh Muḥammad Ghaws̲</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Miniscule rough nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_81A-item2">
                     <locus from="2v" to="2v">f. 2v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 81A b. 
</p>
                        <p>Untitled collection of magical and numerological prescriptions, including magic squares or vifq al-aʿdād, by an unnamed compiler. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Miniscule rough nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_81A-item3">
                     <locus from="3v" to="208r">ff. 3v-208r </locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_19540626">Shaykh Muḥammad Ghaws̲ Gavālyārī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_19540626">شيخ محمّد غوث گواليارى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21953">Javāhir-i khamsah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_21953">جواهر خمسه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 81A c. 
</p>
                        <p>Extensive treatise on esoteric aspects of Sufism and the occult sciences by <persName key="viaf_19540626" role="aut">Shaykh Muḥammad Ghaws̲ Gavālyārī</persName>, or <persName key="viaf_19540626" role="aut">Muḥammad ibn Khaṭīr al-Dīn ibn Laṭīf ibn Muʿīn al-Dīn Qattāl ibn Khaṭīr al-Dīn ibn Bāyazīd ibn Khvājah Farīd al-Dīn Nayshāpūrī ʿAṭṭār</persName> (d. 970/1562), the latter descends from the Ismāʿīlī imams after <persName key="viaf_100648969" role="oth">Imām Jaʿfar al-Ṣādiq</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author wrote the work at the age of fifty, in 956/1549. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 208r): completed by ʿAbd al-Ḥakīm for Ghulām Aḥmad Khān Ṣāḥib, Rajab 1223/August 1808. 
</p>
                        <p>The manuscript is a composite of fragments from different manuscripts of different ages and origins. 
</p>
                        <p>Multiple diagrams. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_81A-item4">
                     <locus from="208v" to="209r">ff. 208v-209r </locus>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22259">Shajarah-'i ʿishqīyah-'i ātish'khvārah-'i Pīrān-i Shaṭṭārīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22259">شجرهٴ عشقيّهٴ آتش خوارهٴ پيران شطّاريّه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 81A d. 
</p>
                        <p>Spiritual genealogy of the <orgName>Shaṭṭārīyah</orgName> Ṣūfī order, beginning with <persName key="person_f8257" role="subject">Sayyid Ghulām Qādir</persName> (d. 1223/1808), traced back to <persName key="viaf_19540626" role="subject">Shaykh Muḥammad Ghaws̲ Gavālyārī</persName>, and thence to <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" role="subject">Imām ʿAlī ibn Abū Ṭālib</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is compiled by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end; datable to late 1808. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is followed by a brief collection of esoteric notes. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
